title: Girls volleyball rankings for Oct. 25, 2015
text:
By Kyle Craig | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 25, 2015 5:00 PM View/Post Comments 
The lehighvalleylive girls volleyball rankings made it through the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference tournament unscathed. 
The top four -- Parkland, Liberty, Nazareth and Central Catholic -- were the four EPC semifinalists, and the top two (the Trojans and Hurricanes) were the conference finalists. 
There was a rare interstate matchup when North Hunterdon took down Notre Dame recently. The Lions later fell to Hunterdon Central in the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex Tournament championship. 
Notre Dame rounds out the top 10 after capturing its first Colonial League title over Southern Lehigh. 
Check out the full rankings by scrolling through the gallery atop this post.
